#English Premier League is selected

matches = read.table('matches.csv', header=TRUE, sep=',')
select_epl=filter(matches, league_id=="148")
select_epl=select_epl %>% mutate(final =match_hometeam_score-match_awayteam_score)
select_epl$finalstatus = ifelse(select_epl$match_awayteam_score==select_epl$match_hometeam_score,"draw",ifelse(select_epl$match_awayteam_score>select_epl$match_hometeam_score,"away","home"))

#missing control for selected variables

slc<- select(select_epl,match_hometeam_score,match_awayteam_score)
missmap(slc)

Home Score histogram&fitting line

gf <- goodfit(select_epl$match_hometeam_score, "poisson")
plot(gf, type = "h", scale = "raw", xlab="Home Goals",ylab="Number of Games")

Away Score histogram&fitting line

Both Home and Away Score are poisson distributed as seen from histograms

gf2 <- goodfit(select_epl$match_awayteam_score, "poisson")
plot(gf2, type = "h", scale = "raw", xlab="Away Goals",ylab="Number of Games")

Home-Away score is calculated and histogram plotted. It fits skellam distribution. (The distribution of the difference between two Poisson Distribution is fitted to Skellam Distribution)

my_data <- as_tibble(select_epl)
my_data=my_data %>% mutate(diff =match_hometeam_score-match_awayteam_score)

h_a<-hist(my_data$diff, prob=TRUE, ylim = c(0, .25),col="purple", xlab="Home Goals - Away Goals ", 
           ylab="Number of Games", main=" ")

quest 2 matches and bets data are joined

bets = read.table('bets.csv', header=TRUE, sep=',')

slc_match<- dplyr::select(select_epl,match_id,epoch, match_status,match_hometeam_score,match_awayteam_score,league_id,finalstatus)
leftJoin <- left_join(slc_match,bets,by="match_id")

Some ids(eg id 13331,13329) not in bets data but available in matches data so inner join is done.

innerJoin <- inner_join(slc_match,bets,by="match_id")
m1=filter(select_epl, match_id=="13329") #control

innercal=mutate(innerJoin,prob=1/value)
innercal=mutate(innercal,epoch_trn=as_datetime(innerJoin$epoch))
innercal=mutate(innercal,oddepoch_trn=as_datetime(innerJoin$odd_epoch))

Bookmakers:Marathonbet,Dotabet,Unibet,Titanbet & Variable:odd_1-odd_2-odd_x are selected

innercalbm=innercal%>%filter(odd_bookmakers %in% c("Marathonbet", "Dotabet","Unibet","Titanbet") & variable %in% c("odd_1", "odd_x","odd_2") )

in some matches (eg match_id = 162714) the odd_1, odd_2, odd_x fields were twice, due to the odd_epoch field.so max date from the odd_epoch field was chosen.

innercalbm_unq=innercalbm %>% group_by(match_id,odd_bookmakers, variable) %>%summarise(max = max(oddepoch_trn))
innercalbm_unqq <- left_join(innercalbm_unq,innercalbm,by = c("match_id" = "match_id","odd_bookmakers"="odd_bookmakers","variable"="variable","max" = "oddepoch_trn"))

normalization step

dtot=innercalbm_unqq %>% 
  group_by(match_id,odd_bookmakers) %>% 
  summarise(totalprb = sum(prob))

innercalbm_unqq <- left_join(innercalbm_unqq,dtot,by = c("match_id" = "match_id","odd_bookmakers"="odd_bookmakers"))
innercalbm_unqq=innercalbm_unqq %>% mutate(normprob =prob/totalprb)

Marathonbet is selected

innercalbm_mar=filter(innercalbm_unqq,odd_bookmakers=="Marathonbet")
x=setDF(innercalbm_mar)
basic_summ_t2 = dcast(x, match_id + finalstatus ~ variable , value.var = "normprob")
## Warning in dcast(x, match_id + finalstatus ~ variable, value.var =
## "normprob"): The dcast generic in data.table has been passed a grouped_df
## and will attempt to redirect to the reshape2::dcast; please note that
## reshape2 is deprecated, and this redirection is now deprecated as well.
## Please do this redirection yourself like reshape2::dcast(x). In the next
## version, this warning will become an error.
basic_summ_t2=basic_summ_t2 %>% mutate(diff =odd_1-odd_2)
summary(basic_summ_t2$diff)
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
## -0.7853 -0.1139  0.1460  0.1433  0.4388  0.8598

for actual prob calculation

basic_summ_t2$interval = ifelse(-1<basic_summ_t2$diff & basic_summ_t2$diff< -0.5,-0.75,ifelse(-0.5<basic_summ_t2$diff & basic_summ_t2$diff<0,-0.25,ifelse(0<basic_summ_t2$diff & basic_summ_t2$diff<0.5,0.25,0.75)))
total=basic_summ_t2 %>%group_by(interval) %>% summarize(n=n())
draws=basic_summ_t2 %>% filter(finalstatus == "draw")
totaldraw=draws %>%group_by(interval) %>% summarize(drawcnt=n())
ttl <- left_join(total,totaldraw,by="interval")
ttl= ttl%>%mutate(sampleprb=drawcnt/n)
ggplot(basic_summ_t2, aes(x = diff, y = odd_x)) +theme_bw() +geom_smooth()+ggtitle("Marathonbet")+xlab("P(home win)  P(away win)") + ylab("P (tie)")+geom_point(data=ttl,aes(x=interval,y=sampleprb),shape=23, fill="red", color="darkred")+geom_point(data = basic_summ_t2, aes(x = diff, y = odd_x),shape=10,fill="white", color="black")
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'

Sample prob>Bookmakers Prob>make money. The trend line for odds was not well matched with the actual results of the matches. quest 3 data prep

goals = read.table('goals.csv', header=TRUE, sep=',')
booking = read.table('booking.csv', header=TRUE, sep=',')

#first case --- 90+ goals
#matches were selected which are change the result of match after 90+ minutes
goals$tm=base::substr(goals$time, 1, 2)
goals$tm <- as.numeric(goals$tm)

goals$homesc=base::substr(goals$score, 1, 1)
goals$homesc <- as.numeric(goals$homesc)

goals$awaysc=base::substr(goals$score, 5, 5)
goals$awaysc <- as.numeric(goals$awaysc)

selc1case=goals%>%filter(tm==90)
selc1case=selc1case %>% mutate(diffsc =abs(homesc-awaysc))

selc1case$case1=ifelse(selc1case$diffsc==0 | selc1case$diffsc==1,1,0)

selcasedel=filter(selc1case, case1==1)

delcase1=anti_join(innercalbm_unqq, selcasedel, by = "match_id")

## "prob"): The dcast generic in data.table has been passed a grouped_df and
## will attempt to redirect to the reshape2::dcast; please note that reshape2
## is deprecated, and this redirection is now deprecated as well. Please do
## this redirection yourself like reshape2::dcast(xd3). In the next version,
## this warning will become an error.
basic_summ_dot3=basic_summ_dot3 %>% mutate(diff =odd_1-odd_2)
summary(basic_summ_dot3$diff)
##     Min.  1st Qu.   Median     Mean  3rd Qu.     Max. 
## -0.87208 -0.24963  0.13824  0.07151  0.32374  0.92087
#for actual prob 
basic_summ_dot3$interval = ifelse(-1<basic_summ_dot3$diff & basic_summ_dot3$diff< -0.5,-0.75,ifelse(-0.5<basic_summ_dot3$diff & basic_summ_dot3$diff<0,-0.25,ifelse(0<basic_summ_dot3$diff & basic_summ_dot3$diff<0.5,0.25,0.75)))
totaldot3=basic_summ_dot3 %>%group_by(interval) %>% summarize(n=n())
drawsdot3=basic_summ_dot3 %>% filter(finalstatus == "draw")
totaldrawdot3=drawsdot3 %>%group_by(interval) %>% summarize(drawcnt=n())
ttldot3<- left_join(totaldot3,totaldrawdot3,by="interval")
ttldot3= ttldot3%>%mutate(sampleprb=drawcnt/n)
ggplot(basic_summ_dot3, aes(x = diff, y = odd_x)) +theme_bw() +geom_smooth()+ggtitle("Dotabet")+xlab("P(home win)  P(away win)") + ylab("P (tie)")+
  geom_point(data=ttldot3,aes(x=interval,y=sampleprb),shape=23, fill="red", color="darkred")+geom_point(data = basic_summ_dot3, aes(x = diff, y = odd_x),shape=10,fill="white", color="black")
